  "prompt": "What's life like in Bhutan?",
  "response": "Life in Bhutan is unique and characterized by several distinctive features:\n\n1. Culture and Religion\n- Predominantly Buddhist\n- Strong emphasis on preserving traditional culture and values\n- Traditional dress is still commonly worn\n- Gross National Happiness is prioritized over GDP\n\n2. Geography and Environment\n- Mountainous terrain with beautiful landscapes\n- Located in the Eastern Himalayas\n- High altitude regions with diverse ecosystems\n- Strong environmental conservation policies\n\n3. Lifestyle\n- Predominantly rural society\n- Agriculture is a major occupation\n- Strong community and family bonds\n- Relatively low-stress lifestyle compared to many other countries\n\n4. Economy\n- Developing economy\n- Limited industrialization\n- Tourism is carefully managed\n- Agriculture and hydroelectric power are key economic sectors\n\n5. Social Characteristics\n- Low population (around 750,000)\n- Limited foreign influences\n- Strong sense of national identity\n- Emphasis on education and healthcare\n\n6. Government\n- Constitutional monarchy\n- Democratic system introduced in 2008\n- Strict regulations on modernization to preserve culture\n- Limited but growing international connectivity\n\n7. Challenges\n- Remote location\n- Limited economic opportunities\n- Infrastructure development in progress\n- Balancing traditional values with modernization\n\nOverall, Bhutan offers a unique blend of traditional culture and gradual modernization.",
